<!-- Game Description Table -->

<table class="tablestyle" id="table14" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td class="sectional">

<!-- Game Description Header -->
		
		<table class="headertable" id="table15" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="2">
			<tr>
				<td class="headercell">
				<img border="0" src="../../../images/headers/gamedes.jpg" width="240" height="33"></td>
			</tr>
		</table>

<!-- Game Description Sectional -->

<table border="0" width="100%" id="table16" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 8pt; color: #FFFFFF; font-weight: bold; text-align: left; background-color: #333333; border-left: 2px solid #000000; border-right: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-top: 2px solid #000000; border-bottom: 2px solid #FFFFFF">
			<br>The year is 1998 and terrorist activity is rampant. All efforts for peace have failed. With no peaceful end in sight, the U.S. Government has funded a top secret Black Operations military group to attack and destroy the terrorists and rescue any hostages. Black Dawn puts you in control of a combat helicopter, the Agile Warrior: F-IIIX, with two flight modes, six views, and thirty-two missions to blast through. Everything else is on a need-to-know basis. A saved game requires one memory block.
			      <br><br>Black Dawn fulfills a few childhood dreams by putting gamers in control of a military helicopter. Terrorists have grown powerful in the world and it is up to you to restore stability and peace throughout the lands. Assigned to a variety of campaigns, you must fly the AH-69 Mohawk (sounds like something Jan-Michael Vincent from AIRWOLF would pilot) as you battle through enemy territory across different global locales.
			      <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Manufacturer's description:</u><br>
                  <br>Step into the cockpit and step into the ride of your life! You are a helicopter pilot with an attitude. Being the best has a price and right now you've got your hands full. Face tough opponents in eight different scenarios with multiple objectives in each mission. But you'll have some of the best hardware available. A vast array of weapons and three different perspectives allow total perception while you're are flying.
                  <br><br>* Become a helicopter pilot--with an attitude!
                  <br>* Eight different scenarios
                  <br>* Multiple objectives to meet
                  <br>* Vast array of weapons
                  <br>* Three different perspectives
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Features:</u><br>
			<ul><li>Third or First person perspectives.</li>
			<li>3D graphics</li>
			<li>Cartoon graphics</li>
			<li>Combat helicopter & Hostage rescue themes.</li></ul>
</td>

	</tr>
	</table>
	       	</td>
     </tr>
</table>  

